.ds n) explain_popen_or_die
.cp 0  \" Solaris defaults to ''.cp 1'', sheesh.
.TH explain_popen_or_die 3
.SH NAME
explain_popen_or_die \- process I/O and report errors
.if require_index \{
.XX "explain_popen_or_die(3)" \
    "process I/O and report errors"
.\}
.SH SYNOPSIS
#include <libexplain/popen.h>
.sp 0.3
FILE *explain_popen_or_die(const char *command, const char *flags);
.SH DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]explain_popen_or_die\fP function
is used to call the \f[I]popen\fP(3) system
call.  On failure an explanation will be
printed to \f[I]stderr\fP,
obtained from \f[I]explain_popen\fP(3),
and then the process terminates
by calling \f[CW]exit(EXIT_FAILURE)\fP.
.PP
This function is intended to be used in a fashion
similar to the following example:
.RS
.ft CW
.nf
FILE *fp = explain_popen_or_die(command, flags);
.fi
.ft R
.RE
.TP 8n
\f[I]command\fP
The command, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]popen\fP(3) system call.
.TP 8n
\f[I]flags\fP
The flags, exactly as to be passed to the \f[I]popen\fP(3) system call.
.TP 8n
Returns:
This function only returns on success, see \f[I]popen\fP(3) for more
information.  On failure, prints an explanation and exits.
.\" ----------------------------------------------------
